Text:
Please explain below points.

System.out.println(new String("ABC").intern()==new String("ABC").intern());

In the above code its print "true". But according java rules, in case of new operator it always create a new object.intern() method create object in string pool. so my question is, in the above code how many object created.

according to me 3 new object will created. one goes to String pool and two anonymous object will created by new operator. But i am not sure.  please explain if i am wrong.
